[SN]TITLE[SN]
UK opposes future migrant rescues - in 15 seconds

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
The UK would not support future search and rescue operations to prevent migrants drowning in the Mediterranean Sea, the Foreign Office has said.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Media playback is unsupported on your device
28 October 2014 Last updated at 16:14 GMT
Foreign Office minister Baroness Anelay has said such operations can encourage more people to attempt to make the dangerous sea crossing to enter Europe.
The announcement comes as EU countries are meeting in Brussels to discuss how to cope with the huge numbers of people making the often treacherous journey across the Mediterranean to Europe.
